# Media Upload Policy

## Never persist inline image data

- **Never** store `data:image/...;base64,...` or `blob:` URLs in localStorage, Supabase columns, or any database field.
- **Never** upload user images to Supabase Storage — this project does not use that pattern.
- **Never** use `FileReader.readAsDataURL()` for images that will be saved to app state or backend.

## File uploads → Cloudinary only

User-facing file pickers must upload via [`uploadImageToCloudinary`](src/lib/cloudinary.ts) (unsigned preset).

Required env (see [`.env.example`](.env.example)):

- `VITE_CLOUDINARY_CLOUD_NAME`
- `VITE_CLOUDINARY_UPLOAD_PRESET`

Reuse [`CloudinaryFileUpload`](src/components/shared/CloudinaryFileUpload.tsx) instead of duplicating upload logic.

## Allowed stored URL formats

Validate with helpers from [`src/lib/media-url.ts`](src/lib/media-url.ts):

| Helper | Use case |
|--------|----------|
| `isPersistableImageUrl` | Cover images, media library, community attachments, hero icons |
| `isPersistableAvatarValue` | Profile avatar (also allows `bg-*` Tailwind class tokens) |
| `sanitizeCommunityImageUrls` | Strip invalid attachments before save |

Allowed values:

- `https://` / `http://` URLs (prefer Cloudinary `secure_url` after upload)
- Static paths: `/heroes/...`, `/traits/...`
- Avatar Tailwind classes: `bg-brand-gold`, etc.

## Validation layers

1. **UI** — block `data:` / `blob:` on paste/input; show error from i18n
2. **DataContext** — guard `addMedia`, `updateMedia`, `addCommunityPost`, `updateCommunityPost`, `addPost`, `updatePost`

## Exceptions (local only, not persisted)

- Team Builder PNG export via `canvas.toDataURL` for browser download only
- html2canvas internal placeholders

## Adding new image upload surfaces

1. Use `CloudinaryFileUpload` for file input
2. Validate manual URLs with `isPersistableImageUrl` before mutation
3. Add DataContext guard if introducing a new persisted entity with image fields
